will not seek re-election. <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> represented the 3rd Congressional District along <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>'s central shorefront. Rep. <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>, D-Calif., the ranking Democrat of the <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Works </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> committee </ORGANIZATION>, is in line to succeed <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> Any new chairman must be approved by the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Democratic Caucus.
