nated the contract in 1984 because of equipment faults. In the civil suit, prosecutors alleged Cubic knowingly presented false claims for payment because some company officials were aware that the detectors had failed the tests. Under an agreement with the <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>, Cubic company will remain a government contractor. `` Since the events leading to the indictment, Cubic has taken the necessary steps to avoid a recurrence of similar conduct,'' <PERSON> Nunez </PERSON> said.
