<TEXT>
 Three small children burned to death in a village in central <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION> while their parents were away, the state news agency <ORGANIZATION> Tanjug </ORGANIZATION> reported Saturday. The agency said a 3-year-old boy and his sisters, aged 2 and 4, died as fire consumed their wooden home in the village of <LOCATION> Imljani </LOCATION>. The village, on <LOCATION> Mount </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vlasic </LOCATION>, is 155 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Belgrade </LOCATION>, the capital. Only their 5-year-old sister was pulled to safety by a neighbor, the agency said.
