<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 State District Judge <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> says he understands a man's fondness for his cowboy hat, but do n't try wearing one in his court. `` The judge asked if I would remove it and said he could give me six months or a $ 5,000 fine,'' said <PERSON> Keven </PERSON> <PERSON> Beaird </PERSON>. `` I told him I would n't, his gavel fell, and it was 10 days in the county jail.'' <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> sentenced the General Dynamics toolmaker for contempt of court Monday for refusing to take off his hat in a jury assembly room. The judge released him three days later after <PERSON> Beaird </PERSON> apologized. `` He said he was sorry, that he knew he had to follow the rules of the court,'' <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> said Friday. `` I told him I admired his belief, but to save himself for the big battles of life.'' District Judge <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Drago </PERSON> said he supports <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON>'s decision. `` I've never heard of specifically a hat. But I've asked people to take off hats before, and no one has ever refused,'' <PERSON> Drago </PERSON> said. `` He must like his hat.'' `` I do n't like anybody to tell me to take my hat off,'' <PERSON> Beaird </PERSON> said. `` I just wo n't do it, but I guess if I go to court again.. well, I believe I would take it off.''
