 <PERSON> Sands </PERSON>, who was working on an air defense systems contract for Easams, a <LOCATION> Marconi </LOCATION> affiliate, died in March 1987 when he drove his car loaded with tanks of gasoline into a vacant restaurant _ <PERSON> Victor </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON>, 46, a <ORGANIZATION> Marconi </ORGANIZATION> scientist who died of a drug overdose in April 1987 His wife told an inquest he had been under strain in his job at Marconi Space and Defense Systems in <LOCATION> Portsmouth </LOCATION>. _ <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>, 23, a lab technician for <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Atomic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION>, whose body was found Feb. 1 halfway down a cliff at <LOCATION> Boscastle </LOCATION> in western <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> Police found a note but have not disclosed its contents.
