<TEXT>
 Shaking down shopkeepers. Taking protection money from criminals. Dealing drugs. Collecting kickbacks. Demanding bribes. This, prosecutors say, is how some municipal employees spend their days. The problem is as old as government and the prognosis for a cure is as bleak as ever. `` There's always going to be people who take advantage of the system. Eight percent of the Apostles were corrupt, and look at who screened them,'' said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Maloney </PERSON>.
